{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10c6354b-3a74-4b0c-a4d8-cc1e9b409b1b","content":"No repo-specific docs here, but I can give you the recommended MSTest setup from my knowledge:\n\n## 1. Simplest project file with MSTest.Sdk\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` brings in MSTest runner, assertions, and the test framework automatically. No `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd a file called **`*.testconfig.json`** (e.g. `mstest.testconfig.json`) or use assembly-level attributes. The simplest way is an `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\n`MethodLevel` runs all test methods in parallel. Use `ClassLevel` if you want parallelism only across classes (methods within a class run sequentially).\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nUse `[DoNotParallelize]` on a test class:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task CanInsertRecord() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task CanQueryRecords() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAny class marked `[DoNotParallelize]` runs after all parallel tests finish, and its methods execute one at a time.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of the three pieces:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `MyTests.csproj` | `Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\"` — zero boilerplate |\n| `AssemblyInfo.cs` | `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]` |\n| DB test class | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b6432f49-21b7-44a1-8dcc-c6194735521f","outputTokens":505,"requestId":"E3C9:23A6C6:1852014:1B4CF14:6A052B31"},"id":"c69b1497-7f4e-4764-a9b9-c6986765570d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:54:05.012Z","parentId":"90f85c30-c978-4e04-a